A conversion kit to turn your regular Aeronautica Imperialis Tiger Sharks (such as from starter set) into AX-1-0 with heavy weapon versions.

For each Tiger Shark, you will need to print:
2x weapons
2x connector pieces
2x body components (you will need to mirror one of these, the other parts don't require mirroring)

To assemble, make sure to SKIP steps 8 and 9 in the Tiger Shark assembly instructions booklet (don't glue in the weapons or missile bays). Glue your printed weapon, connector, and body pieces together, then slot into the areas where the normal weapon and missile bay components would go. They won't friction fit so you will need to glue or magnetise once you're sure they are aligned properly.

The Heavy Rail hasn't worked particularly well on my FDM printer, particularly the interior gap detail. You may have more luck with something more dialed in or with a resin printer.

The Heavy Plasma worked well with FDM once I removed the venting fins from the underside. I've attached the finned versions in case you have more luck.

It is meant for 15mm wargaming, but could possibly be rescaled down to 6mm (Although I don't know if the details from the helmet would still be visible).

There is another version of this model with a Human Auxiliary helmet.

For some reason, it seems that the Fishy Head version is 4 to 5 times the file size than the Human Auxiliary. I am still pretty new to this, so if anyone knows how to fix this issue, step forward!

Death comes in many forms. For this death, it's a ball. Also includes 2 genetic gathering and sampling assistants for free.

For a Devilfish, it's the wrong shape, wrong size, wrong weapon options, and can't technically carry any Kroot, but it's lovely just the same. This was supposed to be a simple joke project that got out of hand. The level of detail isn't the same all over but it's taken up too much of my time and I just need to move on. 

* Comes with open and closed version of the side and back hatches.
* It can either be assembled using 1.75mm filament as alignment pins or 10x2mm magnets.
* Magnets allow for easy breakdown to swap open/closed hatches or easier travel.
* Sides can be printed mirrored for more variety.


You will need heads to complete these models. I recommend purchasing the official box sets for those. Hopefully this will tell THEM that we want more options to add them to our armies.
